\b\fs32 patch naming
\b0\fs24 \
Patch naming conventions could exist to help users locate and organize them; however, the system does not depend on patch names (including special characters) for proper operation - so feel free to name them however you want.  As long as a patch name appears verbatim in a content.json file (or actually any .json file), the system can launch it from its corresponding button. \
